 and insights, the presentation of each school is concluded with a contribution to discussions of educational technologies. In addition to philosophers seeking a valuable and clear structuring of a still burgeoning field, the volume is of interest to those working with educational philosophy and value sensitive design. „Stig Børsen Hansen’s book is a must for all interested in understanding the development of the philosophy of technology and the relation of thoughts of thinkers that have shaped the area. The author presents a new and refreshing take on the ideas from Marx to Marcuse, from Dewey to Latour, and Heidegger to Borgmann. It will engage and hopefully provoke." Dr. Jan Kyrre Berg Friis, University of Copenhagen  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 4aDesign. 4aErziehung. 4aTechnikphilosophie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aPhilosophy of technology.  aeducational philosophy.  avaluesensitive design.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishz978311070482208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110704648oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831106195150 cprintz978311061947840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311062207240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110622072423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.co